        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> <BR>Lifetap was considered a Heal. Its why it has a horrible ratio, its why it never was resisted, it was the massive perk of being a necromancer, having the shitty faction, the group/raid unfriendliness...you get a "take from you, give to me" spell.</P><P>Lifetap was once unresistable(because it was a heal).</P><P>Verant nerfed it.</P><P>Lifetap would be unresistable as long as you were within 6 levels of the target.</P><P>Verant nerfed that too.</P><P>Lifetap was put on "Dragonbreath line"..which was like a old fashion Lure. Early pre-kunark mobs like Dragons and some noobie monsters would have this resist, it never resisted, except for a funky 1 out of 100 occassion.</P><P>Verant nerfed that, also.</P><P>Lifetap in its current form, is sub-Lure in resist.</P><P>Lure -300 Resist<BR>Lifetap -200 Resist<BR>Splurt 0-100 Resist</P><P>Lifetap has over time been reduced in effectiveness, very quietly and slowly.</P><P>On PvP servers, bards are resisting Lifetap, because they can get in the 200 range of Resists.</P><P>However, it still suffers the same ungodly high ratio.</P><P><b>Not even is the necro allowed to return to his old pre-kunark power via Ancient spells.</b></P><P>It's rather funny that the necro cannot be returned to his OLD "too powerful" form, when every other class, and every monster, has jumped 10 times in power.</P><P><font size=1>Super Saigon Potuku defeats Abashibuu!!</font id=size1><BR><img src="http://necro.eqclasses.com/potus/abashibuu.jpg" border=0></font></td>

