        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I think, that lifetaps should be returned to their status as "resistable extremely rarely" or "not resistable at all". We are PAYING much more than we should for a LTap to be pretty much irresistable. I mean, our taps are SLOW to cast, EXPENSIVE when you consider conventional nukes and as HEALS, they are also not mana efficient.</P><P>As a combination, we are almost paying double, and when you can expect to get healed off a mob, you can shoulder the cost of a LTap ... it's reliable, you know it will land and save your butt. Yes, you can get caught flat footed, even with Lich or whatever running, by the possibility of not having enough mana at the time, or interrupts and the like. Considering the standard lifetap, like most of our spells, is freaking slow to cast (OK, Deflux is the wondrous exception, but the mana efficiency of Deflux is kinda kicked in the tail) means a good chance it will be interrupted anyway.</P><P>We are gambling a lot on a lifetap that is technically very unreliable. The only real reliability we have is that it cannot be resisted. It can be interrupted, it's expensive enough that we can run OOM casting it, even with Arch Lich. To have this thing RESIST on us is painful.</P><P>So ... I think of some options:</P><P>1) Keep Ltaps as they are now, and make them unresistable again.<BR>2) Reduce the cost and casting times of Ltaps and leave them resistable.</P><P>Yeah, I know option #2 bites, but it would be better than having slow, expensive, resistable LTaps.</P><P>Saminga Amaranth, 60th Bad Girl of Avatars of Discord, Spankmistress of Rodcet Nife.</P><P>Good girls go to Heaven, bad girls FD and /q out.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
